laboratory_examinations.findings: NEGATIVE FOR LEGIONELLA SEROGROUP 1 ANTIGEN. Reference Range-Negative. A negative result does not rule out infection due to other L. pneumophila serogroups or other Legionella species.

Left lower lobe consolidation with ground-glass opacity and a small associated effusion consistent with pneumonia. Dense consolidation in the right lower lobe with small-to-moderate effusion. Granuloma noted in the right upper lobe.
